ear friend who I spent a lot of time with whose name was Paul Gresham. He had a group called Birthright. And a little bit later in his group he had Ricky Ford.", "doc_title": "Chuck Mancuso interviewed by Monk Rowe, Buffalo, New York, October 10, 2013", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/chuck-mancuso-interviewed-monk-rowe-buffalo-new-york-october-10-2013"}, {"speaker": "Big Nick Nicholas", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "And I heard this little young tenor player, Ricky Ford; he has the right mental attitude.", "doc_title": "67619_Big Nick Nicholas oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67619/"}, {"speaker": "Bobby Watson", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "In the 80s he worked with Sam Rivers, Ricky Ford and George Coleman", "doc_title": "Bobby Watson interviewed by Michael Woods, Clinton, New York, January 19, 1996", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/bobby-watson-interviewed-michael-woods-clinton-new-york-january-19-1996"}]}